{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-documentation-tsx","path":"/docs/handbook/developer-setup","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"fcfe37e2-bc0b-50b8-8e1b-490aa315a726","excerpt":"Cloning the Repository Building from the Command Line Command Line Tools You can build the Lingua Franca compiler and other CLI tools with Gradle usingâ€¦","html":"<h1 id=\"cloning-the-repository\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cloning-the-repository\" aria-label=\"cloning the repository permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cloning the Repository</h1>\n<pre class=\"source-lf language-text\">git clone git@github.com:lf-lang/lingua-franca.git\ncd lingua-franca\ngit submodule update --init --recursive</pre>\n<h1 id=\"building-from-the-command-line\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#building-from-the-command-line\" aria-label=\"building from the command line permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Building from the Command Line</h1>\n<h2 id=\"command-line-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#command-line-tools\" aria-label=\"command line tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Command Line Tools</h2>\n<p>You can build the Lingua Franca compiler and other CLI tools with Gradle using <code>./gradlew clean buildAll</code>.</p>\n<p>There are scripts in <code>bin</code> which you can use to run the compiler or other tools. For instance: <code>./bin/lfc --version</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"epoch\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#epoch\" aria-label=\"epoch permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Epoch</h2>\n<p>The Epoch IDE is in a <a href=\"https://github.com/lf-lang/epoch\">separate repository</a>.\nFollow the instructures there in the <a href=\"https://github.com/lf-lang/epoch/blob/main/README.md\">README file</a>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"running-test\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#running-test\" aria-label=\"running test permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Running Test</h1>\n<p>Lingua Franca comes with unit and integration tests. More details can be found <a href=\"/docs/handbook/regression-tests\">here</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"unit-tests\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#unit-tests\" aria-label=\"unit tests permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Unit Tests</h2>\n<p>The unit tests can be run with Gradle using <code>./gradlew test --tests \"org.lflang.tests.compiler.*\"</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"integration-tests\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#integration-tests\" aria-label=\"integration tests permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Integration Tests</h2>\n<p>All integration tests can be run with Gradle using <code>./gradlew test --tests \"org.lflang.tests.runtime.*\"</code>. By specifying the concrete test class, it is also possible to run only tests for a specific target. For instance the Python tests can be run with <code>./gradlew test --tests \"org.lflang.tests.runtime.PythonTest.*\"</code>. For convenience, there is also a script which can be used for running the integration tests for a specific target. For instance: <code>./bin/run-lf-tests Python</code>.</p>\n<p>Sometimes it is useful to only run a single integration test. This can be done with the <code>runSingleTest</code> Gradle task. For instance: <code>./gradlew runSingleTest --args test/C/src/Minimal.lf</code>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"ide-integration\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ide-integration\" aria-label=\"ide integration permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IDE Integration</h1>\n<p>You will likely want to use an IDE for working with the code base. For development of the core tools, any IDE that integrates with gradle can be used. We recommend our <a href=\"/docs/handbook/intellij\">IntelliJ setup</a>.\nIf you plan to contribute to the Epoch IDE, you should use the <a href=\"/docs/handbook/eclipse-oomph\">Oomph setup for Eclipse</a>.</p>","headings":[{"value":"Cloning the Repository","depth":1},{"value":"Building from the Command Line","depth":1},{"value":"Command Line Tools","depth":2},{"value":"Epoch","depth":2},{"value":"Running Test","depth":1},{"value":"Unit Tests","depth":2},{"value":"Integration Tests","depth":2},{"value":"IDE Integration","depth":1}],"frontmatter":{"permalink":"/docs/handbook/developer-setup","title":"Developer Setup","oneline":"Setting up Lingua Franca for developers.","preamble":""}},"prev":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Contributing","oneline":"Contribute to Lingua Franca.","permalink":"/docs/handbook/contributing"}}},"next":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Website Development","oneline":"Development of the Lingua Franca website.","permalink":"/docs/handbook/website-development"}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"5-developer-setup","slug":"/docs/handbook/developer-setup","repoPath":"/packages/documentation/copy/en/developer/Downloading and Building.md","previousID":"008e847f-8ee6-513a-afab-0995ffce336b","nextID":"6fe7623e-c5ce-509d-9532-9d282ae790cc","lang":"en","modifiedTime":"2023-05-21T23:08:24.358Z"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}